20:07.778 --> 20:09.340
Because words of man can be really convincing.

20:09.381 --> 20:31.535
But what I wanna teach to students is that experiencing and encountering Jesus, when you experience Jesus, when you feel him working in your life, when you see him working in other people's life, when you watch somebody get dunked in the baptism tank, and you hear their story about how they're finding and following Jesus, my eight-year-old just got baptized a couple weeks ago, and she has blown apart my faith and this idea of a child like faith.

20:31.776 --> 20:35.762
When we experience and encounter Jesus, nobody is gonna argue that away from you.

20:37.026 --> 20:42.432
Words of man cannot take that experience away from you when you know that he is working and moving in your life.

20:42.932 --> 20:48.899
And when you can feel that, when you can see that, when you can experience it, then we can experience a perfect peace.

20:49.400 --> 20:54.245
But here's what I've learned recently about experiencing peace through his presence.

20:56.808 --> 21:06.258
In January of 2024, my mom started to experience some pretty intense pain, some pretty severe pain.

21:06.882 --> 21:09.165
not knowing what was happening with it, not really understanding.

21:11.227 --> 21:23.603
It got so bad around her stomach area that even bending over to put on shoes to sit down, to tie them was excruciatingly painful and miserable.

21:24.504 --> 21:35.378
So she went to the doctor, got things checked out, got it figured out, whatever this discomfort was, and found that there was a bunch of fluid buildup and they drained the

21:35.810 --> 21:39.835
ridiculous amount of fluid from her stomach.

21:39.855 --> 21:46.884
This was all taken and tested, all the things that they do with finding unknown things in a human body.

21:48.346 --> 21:52.872
And in February of 2024, my mom was diagnosed with ovarian cancer.

21:54.414 --> 22:04.306
And since January of 2024, she has battled this cancer through chemo treatments, through doctor's appointments,

22:04.994 --> 22:16.311
through walking allies alongside her own mother who was also going through ovarian cancer at the same time, trying to take care of me who I need a lot of help being taken care of, okay?

22:16.591 --> 22:17.733
Pray for my wife too, please.

22:19.876 --> 22:34.738
But since February of 2024 is walking through this whole process, and what I've learned about experiencing peace through the presence of Jesus is my mom has the most unexplainable peace that I've ever seen.

22:37.378 --> 22:49.571
I have spent myself countless nights, hours, days, yelling, angry conversation, asking questions, why?

22:50.312 --> 22:54.717
Trying to ask God how this is even remotely fair.

22:56.298 --> 23:02.805
If you've gone through cancer yourself or you've watched somebody go through it, it sucks.

23:04.267 --> 23:04.807
It's terrible.

23:06.209 --> 23:07.250
And I'm a fixer.

23:07.810 --> 23:12.257
my nature and I want to do everything to fix it.

23:13.178 --> 23:14.199
I wish I could fix it.

23:16.343 --> 23:21.711
Psalm 29, 11 says, the Lord gives strength to his people and the Lord blesses his people with peace.

23:23.233 --> 23:27.359
Here's what I know through watching my mom and her cancer journey.

23:28.801 --> 23:34.790
My mom knows Jesus and I promise you if you ask her, which you can't and she's sitting up here.

23:36.733 --> 23:37.554
If you ask her,

23:38.178 --> 23:41.863
She will tell you that being diagnosed with cancer is one of the biggest blessings she's ever received.

23:44.867 --> 23:56.903
If you ask her, she'll tell you countless stories of how she's been able to help other people find and follow Jesus through what she knows to be true about her relationship with Jesus.

23:56.923 --> 24:05.355
She will tell you all the stories of the people that she has walked alongside of as they're going through their own medical diagnosis, whether it's cancer or not.

24:06.296 --> 24:07.858
She'll tell you the ways that

24:08.002 --> 24:09.344
She has found comfort.

24:09.724 --> 24:10.505
She has found peace.

24:10.525 --> 24:14.270
She has found confidence in knowing that it doesn't matter what the diagnosis says.

24:14.370 --> 24:17.273
If you know the person of Jesus, you know we are going at some point anyways.

24:18.234 --> 24:31.771
Whether it's the cancer or whatever, she will tell you that cancer and the diagnosis has been one of the biggest blessings in her life because the Lord has given her strength and the Lord has blessed her with peace.

24:31.791 --> 24:33.373
A peace that passes all understanding.

24:35.896 --> 24:37.618
I hope I can find peace like that someday.

24:38.786 --> 24:45.294
Sometimes when I think I know peace and I'm reminded of that piece, I know my piece has a long way to go.

24:47.077 --> 24:47.918
So let me ask you this.

24:50.141 --> 24:54.827
Do you know peace in this room right now?

24:54.847 --> 25:04.038
Do you know peace to the single mom in the room that is trying as hard as you can to be everything for your kids?

25:06.041 --> 25:06.962
Do you know peace?

25:08.130 --> 25:13.077
Notice on that question up there that peace is capitalized for a reason because peace is a person.

25:16.341 --> 25:22.028
To the patient in the room that received your own diagnosis, do you know peace?

25:24.271 --> 25:35.506
To the husband in the room that is working countless hours, especially this time of year, to be the provider for your family, do you know peace?

25:38.146 --> 25:43.753
To the person in the room laying in bed at night, feeling the weight of the world on your shoulders.

25:46.717 --> 25:47.819
Do you know peace?

25:51.283 --> 25:59.013
To the person in the room that is thinking about taking their own life into their own hands, even if you're sitting here this morning.

26:00.856 --> 26:01.477
Do you know peace?

26:04.060 --> 26:05.682
Luke 2 14 says, suddenly,

26:06.850 --> 26:20.183
The angel was joined by a vast host of others, the armies of heaven, praising God and saying, glory to God in highest heaven and peace on earth to those who God is pleased.

26:24.868 --> 26:34.738
If you're in the room this morning and Jesus isn't the Lord of your life, if you're in the room this morning and you don't know peace, you can leave this building with peace.

26:36.162 --> 26:37.483
Do not miss that opportunity.

26:38.524 --> 26:50.436
Don't miss the opportunity to leave this building this morning, to walk out these doors, to go out into the Commons, to freeze your butt off as soon as those doors open, and try to survive the world.

26:50.476 --> 26:54.980
Don't do it unless you know the person of peace.

26:55.000 --> 27:05.490
Because I promise you, when life's hardest battles come at you, when the struggle hits, when the questions arise, when the frustration happens, when the anger surfaces,

27:06.274 --> 27:09.158
Just want a little side note, like it's okay to be angry with God.

27:10.179 --> 27:12.262
He wants your anger just as much as he wants your praise.

27:12.422 --> 27:13.123
He wants all of you.

27:13.904 --> 27:24.478
But when those moments hit, who you know Jesus to be, the Prince of Peace, is what makes it all okay.

27:26.080 --> 27:33.970
Jet GBT may be able to describe a perfect world of peace, but let me describe to you the peace that I discovered just this week.

27:37.474 --> 27:43.302
I'm sitting by the fireplace in my living room, reading Psalm 63 in the quiet of my home.

27:46.326 --> 27:51.313
As the sun comes up, I start to hear little voices and footsteps throughout my house.

27:52.975 --> 28:03.470
My girls are getting their morning started by finding our elf Connie, who's probably up to no good, and ripping open a bag of mini muffins and leaving crumbs everywhere they go.

28:05.413 --> 28:06.514
I continue to read

28:07.202 --> 28:15.053
When verse three of Psalm 63 says, your unfailing love is better than life itself.

28:15.914 --> 28:16.796
How I praise you.

28:18.859 --> 28:23.345
I take in a deep breath and I know that everything is going to be okay.

28:25.107 --> 28:28.052
Thank you Jesus for being my peace.

28:30.435 --> 28:31.536
Father God, we thank you for today.

28:33.940 --> 28:35.442
We thank you for your son Jesus.

28:36.354 --> 28:43.941
We thank you for the honor and the privilege of being able to know him.

28:45.683 --> 28:47.345
God, you could have kept Jesus all to yourself.

28:49.346 --> 28:56.633
You could have sent him to this earth to do what he needed to do, brought him back up to heaven and said, they still rejected him, so we'll try again another time.

28:57.614 --> 28:58.135
But you didn't.

28:58.896 --> 29:00.617
You gave us the ability to know peace.

29:03.860 --> 29:05.682
Father, right now I pray over this room

29:06.018 --> 29:20.598
Anybody that might be in this room who is fighting to know peace, struggling to understand where the relationship with Jesus sits, struggling and fighting to know what to do next.

29:23.201 --> 29:25.284
I pray right now that you can give them your peace.

29:26.987 --> 29:29.490
You can allow them to feel the presence of your son and their life.

29:32.962 --> 29:36.066
Father, we thank you for the presence of your son joining us in this room this morning.

29:39.730 --> 29:42.533
Be with us as we continue to worship you and lift your name high.

29:43.414 --> 29:52.845
And be with us as we walk out of this building, knowing that it is only peace that passes all understanding, that we need your peace.

29:54.967 --> 29:56.289
We give this time over to you, Father.

29:57.170 --> 30:00.914
We honor you and glorify you with our voices, with our words, with our hearts,

30:02.050 --> 30:05.308
We pray that it is a sweet aroma to you this morning.

30:06.474 --> 30:08.425
It's your son's precious name, we pray.

30:08.445 --> 30:08.626
Amen.

